## Predict Air Quality

This project builds an Air Quality Forecasting Service for an Air Quality sensor available at https://waqi.info/.

Our model uses the daily mean air temperature at 2 m, the daily total precipitation, the maximum wind speed at 10 m, the dominant wind direction at 10 m, as well as the lag-1, lag-2, and lag-3 day PM2.5 features, and based on these we predict future weather.

For the lag features, since there are no lag values for the first three days, we fill these missing values with the mean of all available PM2.5 observations. During forecasting, we adopt a rolling prediction strategy: we first obtain the prediction for tomorrow, then use this to predict the day after tomorrow, and so on.

The output is a forecast for air quality.
